==Government==
On 30 March 2014, Murtaza Kara<U+00E7>anta ([[Nationalist Movement Party|MHP]]) was elected mayor. The previous mayor, Nevzat Bozku<U+015F> ([[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|AKP]]), was not reelected.<ref>{{Cite news|title=<U+0130>lhan Ak<U+00FC>z<U+00FC>m, Ba<U+015F>kan Nevzat Bozku<U+015F>'u Ziyaret Etti (Ilhan Ak<U+00FC>z<U+00FC>m President Visits Mayor Nevzat Bozkus)|date=18 September 2012|newspaper=Ihlas News Agency|language=Turkish|url=http://www.haberler.com/ilhan-akuzum-baskan-nevzat-bozkus-u-ziyaret-etti-3947206-haberi/|archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20120924001147/http://www.haberler.com/ilhan-akuzum-baskan-nevzat-bozkus-u-ziyaret-etti-3947206-haberi-haberi/|archivedate=24 September 2012|deadurl=no}} Note: archive not available until mid-2013.</ref> The mayor before Bozku<U+015F> was Naif Alibeyo<U+011F>lu ([[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|AKP]]).<ref>{{Cite news|author=Bak<U+0131>rc<U+0131>, Cem|title='Ba<U+015F>kan<U+0131>n karde<U+015F>iyim belediye elimizde' ("We Have the Mayor's Brother")|date=7 December 2007|newspaper=Milliyet Online|language=Turkish|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/12/07/guncel/gun02.html|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20071208152911/http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/12/07/guncel/gun02.html|archivedate=8 December 2007|deadurl=no}}</ref>

== Climate ==
Kars has a [[humid continental climate]] ([[K<U+00F6>ppen climate classification]]: ''Dfb''), with a significant difference between summer and winter temperatures, as well as night and day temperatures, due to its location away from large bodies of water, its high elevation and relatively high latitude. Summers are generally brief and warm with cool nights. The average high temperature in August is {{convert|26|<U+00B0>C|<U+00B0>F|lk=on|abbr=on}}. Winters are very cold. The average low January temperature is {{convert|-16|<U+00B0>C|<U+00B0>F|lk=on|abbr=on}}. However, temperatures can plummet to {{convert|-35|C|1}} during the winter months. It snows a lot in winter, staying for an average of four months in the city. Due to its geographic location of the city in the province, it has a slightly milder climate compared to the surrounding region. Some hills and peaks in the province, especially around the [[Sar<U+0131>kam<U+0131><U+015F>]] region, are [[subarctic]] ([[K<U+00F6>ppen climate classification]] ''Dfc'') due to the higher elevation of the region. Both the summers and winters are colder in this area, with winter temperatures reaching {{convert|-40|<U+00B0>C|<U+00B0>F|lk=on|abbr=on}} more regularly.

